commit.message:
Delete all the Travis stuff and make our own.

We don't need many stages and extra builds. When sending patches
upstream, we'll see how qTox/qTox still builds. In the development we do,
it's very unlikely for us to break these builds.

commit.message:
Add bazel BUILD files for qtox.

For simplicity, we compile all files always, unlike cmake, which selects
files based on platform. Since we know and test the platform in sources
anyway, we might as well use that knowledge to silently do nothing
instead of erroring.
